snippet.title: 8 week postnatal surrogate | 2 months postpartum | UK surrogacy
snippet.description:
Getting over thoughts of not being good enough to post this 8-week postnatal update for you guys. Carrying a baby for someone else can still come with the same thoughts and feelings some women experience after birth.

00:00 Hello
00:19 Holidays not travelling
01:13 Belly out
01:28 Nursing bras for my spaniel's ears
02:10 Stretch marks and linea negra
03:11 Waist and hip measurements
03:29 Baby weight loss
03:58 Looking 6 months pregnant
04:20 Diastasis recti
04:37 8-week check up, doctor sign off
05:18 Couch to 5k running and core workout
06:32 Hormone shift as a surrogate
07:17 Fake it til you make it
08:18 Deferring my degree?
08:35 Surrogate baby update
10:23 Surrogacy is the most incredible achievement of my life
11:32 A sense of completion
12:04 Last postnatal update?
13:22 Travel plans

About me: 
I am happily child-free but I've always had a curiosity about pregnancy. I decided to follow in my Mum's footsteps by becoming a traditional surrogate; which means I got pregnant using artificial insemination to create a family for a wonderful couple. Extreme babysitting for 9 months, followed by maternity leave for 12 months to travel the world 🌍 

Professional enquiries:
thetravellingsurrogate@gmail.com 

Buy me a beer?
https://www.buymeacoffee.com/surrogatetravel 

Socials:
https://www.instagram.com/thetravellingsurrogate/?hl=en 
https://www.instagram.com/thehungrysurrogate/?hl=en 

COTS surrogacy agency https://www.surrogacy.org.uk/

Canon In D For Two Harps by Kevin MacLeod
